      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Melbourne ¶ 12 June 1880 ¶ To W. H. Odgers Esqr ¶ Undersecretary. ¶ Sir...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">80.06.12</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To William Odgers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">R80/5900, unit 1154, VPRS 3991/P inward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Melbourne</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12 June 1880</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">To W. H. Odgers Esqr</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Undersecretary.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have the honor to ask, whether you will be so kind to bring under the favorable consideration of the honorable the Chief Secretary, that I am very eager to give to the researches of my Department in the coming financial year the greatest extension possible under the present limitation of my Departmental Service, especially in consideration of the forthcoming exhibition;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>International Exhibition, Melbourne, 1880-1.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and I beg therefore to ask, whether Mr Ramsay would be so kind as to restore on the estimates the £50, which I deducted from the budget of my establishment, as submitted for the new finance year.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to W. Odgers, 23 April 1880<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(in this edition as 80-04-23a).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>This reduction was made in response to your circular, a few month ago received, but — small as it is — it falls very heavily on my Department, which is already so very much less provided than any other scientific institution under the Government.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>On 12 June 1880,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Odgers sent a minute to R. Ramsay: 'Baron Müeller now asks that the £50 by wh he reduced his Contingent Estimates may be restored. There will<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>not be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>[…]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>if the C. S. authorise<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>it to be done — I recomend it for approval'. Ramsay approved Odgers's<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>recommendation the same day.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>your obedient</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
         </div>
